    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm not sure if this is an iTerm2 bug (https://gitlab.com/gnachman/iterm2/-/issues/12212) or a neovim bug, but on v0.11.0 when resizing a terminal window or split pane, Neovim doesn't update it's size accordingly. :redraw does nothing either.\n\nThis only seems to be happening in iTerm2 - Ghostty and Terminal.app work fine. Vim *also* works fine in iTerm2.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\nresize window/iterm2 pane\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNvim resizes with the terminal like it does in Terminal.app and Ghostty\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, Vim works\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMacOS 15.3.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2 Build 3.5.11\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nGithub Releases",
